The paper deals with automatic question generation, which is a task related to natural language processing and machine learning. The proposed model uses neural networks and attention mechanisms, which are common techniques in the sub-fields of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of beam search, which is a common technique in neural language generation (cs.NE) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
